HEADWORD: Sternbergite
<hw>Stern"berg*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after
Count Kaspar <ets>Sternberg</ets> of Prague.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A sulphide of silver and iron, occurring in soft flexible laminae
varying in color from brown to black.</def>⟦br⟧
